brcdSPXGlobalConfigCBState.name: brcdSPXGlobalConfigCBState
brcdSPXGlobalConfigCBState.description: Configure CB (Control Bridge) state for 802.1BR feature on the global level. The set operation is allowed only on CB device. none: reserve state. enable: 802.1BR is enable on CB. disable: 802.1BR is disable on CB. The none state will be displayed if it is not a CB device

brcdSPXGlobalConfigPEState.name: brcdSPXGlobalConfigPEState
brcdSPXGlobalConfigPEState.description: Configure PE (Port Extender) state for 802.1BR feature on the global level. The set operation is allowed only on PE standalone device. none: reserve state enable: 802.1BR is enabled on PE. disable: 802.1BR is disabled on PE. Note that enabling/disabling PE takes effect only after system is saved configure and reloaded. The none state will be displayed if it is not a PE device

brcdSPXConfigUnitPESPXPort1.description: A PE SPX port on PE unit. It returns 0 if SPX port does not exist. Note that the maximum PE SPX port on a PE unit is 2.

brcdSPXConfigUnitPESPXPort2.name: brcdSPXConfigUnitPESPXPort2
brcdSPXConfigUnitPESPXPort2.description: A PE SPX port on PE unit. It returns 0 if SPX port does not exist. Note that the maximum PE SPX port on a PE unit is 2.

brcdSPXConfigUnitPESPXLag1.name: brcdSPXConfigUnitPESPXLag1
brcdSPXConfigUnitPESPXLag1.description: A list of interface indices which are the port membership of a SPX LAG group on PE. Each interface index is a 32-bit integer in big endian order. It returns NULL if PE SPX LAG does not exist. Note that the maximum PE SPX LAG on a PE unit is 2. Each SPX LAG group contains up to 16 ports.

brcdSPXConfigUnitPESPXLag2.name: brcdSPXConfigUnitPESPXLag2

It returns NULL if PE SPX LAG does not exist. Note that the maximum PE SPX LAG on a PE unit is 2. Each SPX LAG group contains up to 16 ports.

brcdSPXConfigUnitRowStatus.name: brcdSPXConfigUnitRowStatus
brcdSPXConfigUnitRowStatus.description: This object is used to delete row in the table and control if they are used.
